						               													<description>Tutti in fattoria is a cooperative and memory game, in which the players have to bring the puppies back to the farm before the wolf arrives.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The box contains 4 environments of the farm with 12 shaped and detachable puppies, 12 hiding places (bush, fence and bale of hay), 1 die, 1 wolf and 1 path.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To become familiar with the game materials, children can combine the 4 environments in a single scenario and try to insert the puppies in the right place, next to their mothers, as in a puzzle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game, the players remove the 12 puppies and put them under the 12 hiding places: the aim of the game is to bring the puppies back into their respective environments.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The current player rolls a die and discovers a hiding place. If there is a puppy inside, he puts it in the respective environment, next to his mother. If the die shows the wolf, it advances on the path.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has 3 modes that require progressively more memory. For example, in the simplest mode the hiding place remains uncovered, while in the advanced rules the hiding places are covered.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
